Package au.edu.anu.twcore.experiment.runtime

Interface MultipleDataLoader<T extends fr.cnrs.iees.properties.SimplePropertyList>

All Known Implementing Classes:
BOMWeatherLoader, CsvFileLoader, OdfFileLoader, TableDataLoader
public interface MultipleDataLoader<T extends fr.cnrs.iees.properties.SimplePropertyList>

A MultipleDataLoader is a class that loads data from a single source (usually a file) into multiple 3Worlds internal objects of the SimplePropertyList hierarchy (usually TwData). The results are grouped in a map of objects by String identifiers. In other words:

1 file <---> 1 MultipleDataLoader <---> 1 Map<String,SimplePropertyList descendant> ---> n TwData

A new MultipleDataLoader class should be defined for any new file format used to input data into 3Worlds. The implementing class must link to the data source in its constructor. cf as an example TableDataLoader.

The identification of separate TwData items in the data files assumes the existence of some unique identifier field in the data, that must be specified in the configuration graph structure.

    • load

      void load​(Map<DataIdentifier,​T> result, T dataModel)
      loads data into a Map of TwData (or other SimplePropertyList implementation, specified by T) indexed by String identifier (typically names of nodes). This will only read properties matching the dataModel argument
      Parameters:
      dataModel - - a T instance that will be cloned as many times as necessary to receive all data contained in the file. Clones are then put in the Map argument.

    • load

      void load​(Map<DataIdentifier,​T> result)
      Loads data into a Map of propertyLists. It uses internally an ExtendablePropertyList and will read all data found in the files, creating properties on demand. This will read everything and put them in propertylists.
